A R E S O L U T I O N
Honoring the Elyria Foundry on its One Hundred
Twentieth Anniversary.
WHEREAS, The members of the Senate of the 136th General Assembly 1
of Ohio are pleased to commend the Elyria Foundry on the auspicious 2
occasion of its One Hundred Twentieth Anniversary; and 3
WHEREAS, Recognition of this prestigious milestone is a fitting 4
tribute to the Elyria Foundry, for throughout the past one hundred 5
twenty years, this fine business has attained a remarkable record of 6
service to the area. Founded in 1905, the company produces all grades 7
of gray and ductile iron castings for numerous industries and employs 8
more than two hundred people, and it also offers manufacturing 9
training opportunities to students from Lorain County Joint Vocational 10
School; and 11
WHEREAS, The success of the Elyria Foundry is a justifiable source 12
of pride and an outstanding reflection not only on the venture itself 13
but also on its astute management and hard-working employees. Due to 14
their vision and initiative, this respected enterprise has earned the 15
gratitude and appreciation of many satisfied customers, and it is 16
truly deserving of high praise; and 17
WHEREAS, Over the decades, the Elyria Foundry has enhanced the 18
quality of life within the surrounding area. We are certain that as 19
this noteworthy establishment maintains its unfaltering dedication to 20
service and achievement, it will continue to prosper and will uphold 21
the tradition of excellence that has long been its hallmark; therefore 22
be it 23
RESOLVED, That we, the members of the Senate of the 136th General 24
Assembly of Ohio, in adopting this Resolution, applaud the Elyria 25

